{"id": "bzcsin", "title": "Amazon launches a credit card for the \u2018underbanked\u2019 with bad credit", "selftext": "&gt; Synchrony Financial and Amazon are partnering on a credit card for those  who might not have good enough credit to get one otherwise. \n\nIt's a cash secured credit card with 28.24% interest.\n\nNever heard of a cash secured credit card, but it apparently means your deposit equals your credit limit.  \n\n&gt; This new Amazon card could open the door to a huge segment of U.S. buyers. According to a 2018 FICO [survey](https://www.fico.com/blogs/risk-compliance/average-u-s-fico-score-hits-new-high/),  more than 11% of the population has a credit score below 550. About 4%  of the population has a  \u201cbad credit score,\u201d which according to FICO  Score is between 300 and 499. Meanwhile according to a 2017 [survey](https://www.cnbc.com/2019/03/08/25percent-of-us-households-are-either-unbanked-or-underbanked.html) by the FDIC, 25% of U.S. households are either unbanked or underbanked. \n\nSource: [https://www.cnbc.com/2019/06/10/amazon-launches-a-credit-card-for-the-underbanked-with-bad-credit.html](https://www.cnbc.com/2019/06/10/amazon-launches-a-credit-card-for-the-underbanked-with-bad-credit.html)", "created_utc": 1560261326, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/bzcsin/amazon_launches_a_credit_card_for_the_underbanked/", "is_self": true}